**Spain to Become Most Visited Country in the World by 2040, Study Predicts**
A study by Google and Deloitte predicts that Spain will surpass France as the most visited country in the world by 2040, with 110 million tourists per year. The study attributes Spain's popularity to its family-friendly hotels, golden sand beaches, and diverse culinary options. The predicted 110 million visitors would represent a 24% increase from the 84 million tourists who visited Spain in 2023. This influx of tourists is expected to lead to the opening of new restaurants, bars, and hotels to accommodate the growing crowds. However, there are growing concerns about overtourism in Spain, with protests and calls for an environmental tax on tourists. The city of Barcelona has even announced that it will no longer grant permits for short-term vacation rentals by 2029 due to the negative impacts of excessive tourism.
