**Spanish Government to Approve 2.5% Salary Increase for Public Employees in 2024**
The Spanish government will approve a 2.5% salary increase for public employees in 2024, effective from January, according to the CCOO and UGT unions. This increase is part of the agreement signed by the government with the unions, which includes a 2% fixed increase and an additional 0.5% based on the evolution of the IPCA. The agreement states that if the IPCA variation from 2022-2024 exceeds the accumulated retributive increase of those years (8%), the additional and consolidable 0.5% increase will be applied. According to the National Institute of Statistics, the IPCA in 2022 was 5.5% and in 2023 was 3.3%, resulting in a total of 8.8%, exceeding the established limit. Therefore, the salary of public employees will increase by 2.5%, even without knowing the 2024 inflation data. The PSOE and Sumar parties had attempted to accelerate the salary increase through an amendment, but the government has decided to approve the 2.5% increase in the Council of Ministers instead.
