**Spanish Government Proposes Record-Breaking Public Employment Offer of 40,000 Positions**
The Spanish government has proposed a public employment offer of 40,000 positions for 2024, with half of them being open to external candidates and the other half being internal promotions. The offer is subject to approval by the Council of Ministers. The offer is the highest ever made, surpassing the 39,574 positions offered in 2023. The government has committed to reserving 10% of the positions for people with disabilities and 2% for people with intellectual disabilities. The offer has been welcomed by UGT, but rejected by CSIF and CCOO, who argue that it maintains the 10% replacement rate and reduces the creation of net employment. The offer also does not guarantee the execution of the deadlines and does not include the inclusion of temporary workers in the promotion process.
