The Spanish government has proposed a record-breaking public employment offer for 2024, exceeding 40,000 positions. The offer includes 21,000 open positions, 10,600 internal promotions, and 8,500 jobs for the Security Forces and Corps. The total number includes 3,000 vacant positions from the past two years that will be re-offered. The final figure will be confirmed when the Council of Ministers approves the Public Employment Offer for 2024, expected to happen in June. The government guarantees that the new offer will create net employment, meaning the number of offered positions will be higher than the vacancies caused by retiring officials. The government and unions have been negotiating the proposal, but the unions have not endorsed it. Only UGT has expressed satisfaction with the proposal, while CSIF rejects it as insufficient and Comisiones Obreras regrets that the number of administrative staff is not increasing.
