**Spanish Civil Guard Intervenes 58,000 Counterfeit Articles Valued at 22 Million Euros**
The Spanish Civil Guard, as part of the 'IMITA' operation, has intervened 58,000 counterfeit articles valued at 22 million euros. The operation, which began in January, aimed to investigate crimes against industrial property and inspect 80 businesses in Tenerife, La Palma, La Gomera, and El Hierro. In the first operation, agents intervened 24,500 counterfeit articles, inspected businesses, and identified 39 people. In a second operation, they intervened over 33,500 high-end counterfeit articles valued at nearly 16 million euros, investigated 45 people, and inspected 39 businesses, mostly bazaars, and four cargo vans. The operation was carried out by the Fiscal Analysis and Border Unit (UDAIFF) of the Tenerife North and South Airport Fiscal Section, along with members of the Fiscal and Border Patrol (PAFIF's) of the territorial companies and Judicial Police agents.
