**Big Russian Encyclopedia Faces Shutdown Due to Unpaid Hosting Services**
The 'Big Russian Encyclopedia' is facing the possibility of shutting down due to unpaid hosting services. The Federal Tax Service has arrested the project's accounts, and the encyclopedia's servers may be disconnected on June 17. The encyclopedia, which was established in 2019 with the aim of replacing Wikipedia, has not been able to pay its authors and experts for their work. The project has received almost 2 billion rubles in government funding since 2019, but has not been able to sustain itself. The encyclopedia's president, Herman Klimenko, believes that the project will receive funding again, but with changes. Experts, such as Yuri Zlobin, president of the Association for the Protection of Intellectual Property 'Russian Shield', believe that the project had good intentions, but a wrong strategy. The encyclopedia is populated with 25,000 new articles each year, compared to Wikipedia's 2 million articles in the same period.
