**Campaña '1m2 contra la basuraleza': Limpieza de espacios naturales en España**
Over 15,000 volunteers participated in the '1m2 against litter' campaign, a joint initiative by Proyecto Libera, SEO/BirdLife, and Ecoembes, to clean up 926 natural spaces in Spain. The campaign aims to combat littering and promote environmental awareness. The eighth edition of the campaign took place on the occasion of World Environment Day, which will be celebrated on June 5th. The campaign received support from organizations such as the Red Cross, ANSE, Paisaje Limpio, Oceánidas, and Adenex, as well as 193 public administrations. The coordinator of Proyecto Libera, Miguel Muñoz, emphasized the importance of citizen participation in natural conservation and highlighted that the campaign goes beyond a simple cleaning action, calling for a social movement to eradicate the problem of abandoned waste and ensure a healthy planet for future generations. The delegate of Ecoembes, Rosa Trigo, stressed the continuous commitment of Libera to mobilize society towards a culture of environmental care and emphasized the goal of expanding the network of Liberators to involve more people in the solution and stop being part of the problem of litter in natural spaces.
