**Spain to Receive Over 90 Million Tourists by End of Year, Says Minister**
Spanish Industry and Tourism Minister Jordi Hereu has stated that Spain will definitely receive more than 90 million international tourists by the end of the year, surpassing the 84 million visitors in 2023. Hereu emphasized the importance of the tourists' spending capacity, which reached 108 billion euros in 2023. He believes that Spain is the first tourist destination, although official data places it second after the United States. Hereu emphasized the need to transform the tourism model, focusing on sustainability and avoiding negative effects on local residents. He outlined the keys to transforming tourism in Spain, including desegmentation, decentralization, creation of new experiences, diversification of the offer, and distribution of benefits across the geography.
